1. The Saints easily could have pulled out the W, if not for trash play by their secondary, and a couple of (typical) REALLY bad calls/non-calls.

2. The Saints D, but especially their secondary, need to wake the hell up. Their "get Brees another ring" window is closing, yet they're playing sleepy.


3. People who said Teddy should still be starting need to not watch football anymore. Teddy played solid and helped the team get 5 wins with Brees out. Brees just put up one of the TOP 3 ranked QB performances of all time, in NFL HISTORY. That is the difference. He is capable of that, and arguably the best passer in NFL history. Teddy is and has only ever been solid, that's it.



4. This Saints team can still go all the way. They could have beaten the NFC's top team had it not been for a couple of dumb plays, even WITH bad D coverage. That D needs to wake the hell up and back Brees up. The man helped put up 46 damn points, 6 total TDs himself, and it wasn't enough, even with dumb flags/non-flags? That's ridiculous. The 49ers scoring 48 is 100% on that D. If they want to help Brees GET to, let alone win another SB, they had better start playing like it.
